{"questionId":"27658","questionHtml":"<p>Consider the curve with equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Show that the curve has no local maximum or local minimum points for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt at implicit differentiation, including use of the product rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>at a local maximum or minimum point,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><br>since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math> there are no solutions&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence there are no local maximum or minimum points&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27658","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.7","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Consider the curve with equation x2+y2y2=4x2 where x≥0 and -2<y<2. Show that the curve has no local maximum or local minimum points for x>0.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"7","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.14—Implicit functions, related rates, optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}